title: For Sale:  "PSL-54C" (Romanian Sniper Rifle- 7.62x54)
postcontent:
Hi, I have a Like New "PSL-54" (7.62x54r- Designated Marksman's Rifle/ Eastern Sniper Rifle). This rifle is Romania's Version of the famous "Dragunov" Sniper rifle, Semi Auto with Two 10 round magazines. As of 2010, these rifles were no longer Imported into the US (permanently). Many say this is by far the best Rifle that has ever came from "Century Arms", and are now a rare find/investment rifle, or a great shooter. $1250-$1300 is going rate for these when NOT getting ripped off, but I see them as high as $1600-1800 on Gunbroker if one is even listed.)

 I'm selling cheap being the $125 scope doesn't come with it and I would like to buy a Rifle which I already have ammo for. This was the "Oddball" in my collection, although I couldn't decide if I wanted to keep it "Like-New" or shoot targets out to 600 yards, but I've decided to sell it.

 It has ALL Matching # Parts all the way down to the dust cover, Two "10 round Mags" (Highest capacity mag they make for this rifle.) This Precision "PSL-54" has been in "De-humidified storage" for 5 years and every 6 months I have lubed the Rifle/Bore. Rifle feels/looks Brand New, only 8 rounds of "Winchestor Brass ammo" were put through this rifle and then it was stored. In the Eastern Countries, Its a "Sniper Rifle", in the US, its called a "Designated Marksman's Rifle" being the US has more advanced sniper type Rifles.

This "PSL-54" was imported from the "Cugir Factory in Romania" and is in 98% condition (I say that being 8 rounds fired were through it, had no ear plugs so didnt fire anymore and has been stored ever since...Its literally "LIKE-NEW".) Has beautiful blonde wood also and a tight action/ tight receiver unlike any AK pattern rifle I've ever felt (which AKM's normally have a wobbly Bolt Carriers, this PSL has no wobble nor even any wiggle to it.)

 Comes with 2 magazines. It doesn't have the "PSOP- 4x24 SCOPE" that normally came with this model (Low end Russian "PSOP" scope), but luckily you can purchase a better PSOP for $100-150 if you want a traditional Russian Scope that is better than the standard scope that came with PSL's.

 I'm Selling this Rifle for the rock bottom price of $950 FTF (Face to Face). These Rifles are going from 1200-1800 right now online being they are Rare and will only continue to rise in price. People are either hoarding these, or selling them high priced like "Saiga" Rifles. I've listed this at a rock bottom price. I would like to sell this to fund another Rifle of a different caliber. 

Absolutely NOTHING wrong with this awesome Rifle, it just needs a new home. Again, it LITERALLY is "LIKE-NEW", was going to include the box but cannot find it at the moment but am still looking so may have it when its time to sell.

EMAIL ME IF YOUR INTERESTED (and for more Details/Pics)!! If I do not sell it locally within a couple of days, I will remove listing and place on Gunbroker or a Forum Market, but being things are easier face to face, I would rather avoid the Bidding process, Money Orders, and Shipping charges involved with Gunbroker. Although I will do so if I have no takers within a couple of days.

Hope to hear from you, I am in the Fayetteville Area so if you are nearby, Email me and we can talk about the Rifle more in depth.

Thanks for looking!!

Kimber model 82G... the best government waste ever! US Gov't ordered 20,000 of these precision target rifles for smallbore competition. They then left them in the packaging until someone decided to inventory them by slashing open the package with a razor knife. This is the signature of the kimber 82G is a thin razor-groove cut in the stock. (THIS ONE WAS HAND PICKED AND HAS NO CUT IN THE STOCK)

The 82G is a single-shot, 1-in-16 twist, Heavy Competition barrel (25") bolt action firearm. It was built to the standard of being sub-MOA rifles. The butt stock is adjustable for Length of Pull and all spacers are included. stock is walnut and has some beautiful tiger-striping that doesn't really show in the pictures. Sling swivel is adjustable to the shooter. Sights are anschutz at 1/5MOA per click. Trigger is factory set for 3.5 lbs but is fully adjustable for takeup, pullweight and overtravel. It breaks like glass.

If you are looking to get into smallbore competitive shooting, this is simply the least expensive way to get in without dumping 1400 bucks into the lower-end anschutz rifles. 

This rifle is UNFIRED. It was bought as new (non-rusty) from the CMP when they still had these. The stock HAS NO CUT IN IT. This one was hand selected from the South Store in Anniston. The finish and stock are flawless. This rifle is unfired.It was brought it home, given a complete disassembly, cleaned it thoroughly and put it back in the safe. title: For Sale:  Storm Lake Threaded Barrel for Glock 29/29SF
postcontent:
Before responding, please read the ad.  This ad in the "Gun Parts" section is for a barrel only, not a complete firearm.  If you already own a Glock 29 and are looking to get more velocity out of it, put a silencer/compensatro on it or want to shoot hardcast loads like Buffalo Bore accurately - keep reading. 

This ad is for a drop in (no fitting required) Storm Lake Threaded Barrel w/ Threaded end protector. 416R stainless Barrel is 4.48" long (stock is 3.78" long).  Under 50 rounds down barrel.

Advantages over stock - 

The added length will bring your projectile velocities up to the full size Glock 20 levels.  

The Storm Lake barrel also has a fully supported chamber so you can shoot full power 10mm loads without getting "glock smiles" in the brass".  If you reload you want this.

Match grade broach rifled bore allows you to shoot jacket or hard cast lead bullets.  These types of bullets can lead up the stock barrel or tumble when shot thru a stock barrel.

No Trades.  This is less than I paid so price is firm.

title: For Sale:  Model 1841 Harpers Ferry 1853 Attic Find
postcontent:
The barrel is 33" long, bore measures .54 Cal. using my calipers and the rifling is in really nice shape. From the research I found these barrels were browned and this one has some surface rust over that. I know better than to "clean" it with anything harsh. When I wiped it with a light oil some of the rust/dirt came off and you can see the brown finish in places. It looks like this rifle was kept in the attic and not out in the barn. 

Lock stamped Harpers Ferry, 1853, behind the hammer and and has the eagle in front of it. The barrel tang is stamped 1853. There is a letter s stamped on the right barrel flat just in front of the bolster.

The letters W W over P are stamped on the left side of the barrel. I can see some other markings behind those but can't make them out. From the little I was able to learn these were proof marks. They are there but tough to make out. It has the correct brass front sight and rear V notch.
It does look like someone, at sometime in its life, dropped the rifle muzzle down. You can see that in the pic of the muzzle/rifling.

The letters J L B are stamped on the left of the stock above the trigger and inside the patch box. There is a spare nipple in the box. The ramrod is a steel tulip tip.

This rifle was used. There is some checking in the stock behind the lock. It looks like the wood has dried out and the grain lines opened up a little. They really don't look like cracks but it's tough to tell. The are various nicks and dings in the wood but no other splits or cracks that I can see.

The lock functions fine. The hammer spring is really strong and there is no play or slop in the trigger. There are still some fine traces of the case color on the lock behind the hammer. 

The steel has no pitting in it just an overall brown "patina". The brass is tarnished but not beat up. The rear band has a small scratch in it and the butt plate has a few dings in the top edge.

ASKING $2100.00 Plus Shipping/Ins. to your address

You can email me for more pics at REDACTED

Thanks

H&K USP Tactical in .45ACP with threaded barrel and MkII Taclight. Pistol comes with case, 2 magazines, thread protector, and faux suppressor barrel extension. Pistol is in excellent condition with less than 200 rounds through it. Both Taclight and thread protector are H&K brand. Adjustable sights. 10+1 capacity. 

Enhanced versions of the USP, the USP Tactical models are designed for users who need the features found on the HK Mark 23, but in a more compact pistol. Both pistols approach the precision found on the Mark 23 by adding an extended threaded barrel with a rubber O-ring, adjustable trigger, and adjustable target-type sights. Originally designed for the American market, the USP (Universal Self-loading Pistol) has found international acceptance as an accurate and ultra-reliable handgun. 

Features favored by U.S. law enforcement and military users provided much of the design criteria for the USP. The controls are uniquely American, influenced by such famous designs as the Government Model 1911 pistol. All USPs use a fiber-reinforced polymer frame stiffened by stainless steel inserts at areas subject to stress and friction. HK pioneered this use of polymer materials in the production of handguns more than 30 years ago with the development of the VP70Z and P9S pistols. The USP control lever, a combination safety and decocking lever, is frame mounted and quickly accessible, unlike the slide-mounted safeties common on many semi-automatic pistols. Using a modified Browning-type action with a special patented recoil reduction system, the USP recoil reduction system reduces recoil effects on pistol components and also lowers the recoil forces felt by the shooter. This same recoil reduction system has been tested and proven in the HK Mark 23 pistol developed for the U.S. Special Operations Command. The USP recoil reduction system is insensitive to ammunition types and requires no special adjustment or maintenance. It functions effectively in all USP models. 

The modular design of the USP's internal components allows the control lever function to be switched from the left to the right side of the pistol for left-handed shooters. The USP can also be converted from one type of trigger firing mode to another. This includes combination double-action and single-action (DA/SA) modes and double action only (DAO) modes.

title: For Sale:  Astra Model 400 9mm Largo or .38ACP. (NOT 9mm Luger)
postcontent:
Serial # 712XX 

The Astra Model 400 is known for its ruggedness and reliability. This gun is very clean, with no rust and a clean bright bore. There is slight tarnish on chromed trigger.

Comes with 93 rounds of ammunition.

Good as a collector or shooter.

While Ammo has been a bit scarce in the past, large lots of 1960's and 1970's ammo show up now and then. The good news is that at the last few gun shows that I attended, I noticed that some reloaders are now stocking newly made Largo ammo. New Largo brass is available from Starline, and it can be reloaded using 9mm Luger dies. You can also custom load .38 Super to shoot in this gun

Gun will function with .38 Super ammo, but don't do it, as the pressure in commercial .38 Super is higher than with Largo ammo, and you might damage the gun or yourself.

My research indicates that this gun was made in 1937. I have shot it, and it functioned perfectly for me.

Since this gun is over 50 years old, it is considered a Curio and Relic it DOES NOT require a background check for private transfer under Colorado law.

I will, however, require a valid Colorado photo ID.
